\f0\b\fs24 \cf2 \cb3 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The Complete Guide to AI Agent Configuration: Structure, Memory, and Personality Files\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\cf2 1. The Big Picture: Why Markdown Files?\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \cf2 In 2025\'962026, a remarkable convergence happened across the AI industry. Three independent, high-value projects \'97\'a0
\f0\b Manus
\f1\b0 \'a0(acquired by Meta for $2B),\'a0
\f0\b OpenClaw
\f1\b0 \'a0(145K+ GitHub stars), and\'a0
\f0\b Claude Code
\f1\b0 \'a0(Anthropic's official tool) \'97 all landed on the same architectural pattern:\'a0
\f0\b plain Markdown files as the backbone of AI agent configuration and memory
\f1\b0 .\
This is sometimes called\'a0
\f0\b "Memory as Documentation"
\f1\b0 \'a0\'97 as opposed to the "Memory as Database" approach favored by frameworks like LangGraph or CrewAI. The key insight is that file-based memory is persistent, transparent, human-editable, version-controllable, portable, and cost-effective. While many companies spent millions building vector databases and complex RAG pipelines, the winning pattern turned out to be surprisingly simple.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \cb4 \strokec4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 2. The Core File Architecture\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \cf2 A modern AI agent workspace is defined by a set of Markdown files, each with a distinct purpose. Think of them as the "organs" of your agent. Here's the full anatomy:\
