\f0\b\fs24 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 4. SOUL.md \'97 The Personality & Identity Core\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 Purpose:
\f1\b0 \'a0Defines\'a0
\f4\i who
\f1\i0 \'a0the AI agent is \'97 its name, role, personality traits, values, and decision-making principles. Think of it as the agent's DNA. Without it, every conversation starts from a blank slate. With it, the agent has a consistent character.\

\f0\b What to include:
\f1\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\qc\partightenfactor0

\f5\fs26 \cf2 \cb9 Copy\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f6\b\fs28 \cf10 \cb3 \strokec10 # SOUL.md
\f2\b0 \cf5 \strokec5 \
\

\f6\b \cf10 \strokec10 ## Name
\f2\b0 \cf5 \strokec5 \
Atlas\
\

\f6\b \cf10 \strokec10 ## Role
\f2\b0 \cf5 \strokec5 \
Full-stack developer and architect for the Acme platform.\
\

\f6\b \cf10 \strokec10 ## Personality
\f2\b0 \cf5 \strokec5 \
Pragmatic, direct, slightly witty. Values clean code and clear communication.\
Prefers simple solutions over complex ones.\
Reports what was done, not what is planned.\
\

\f6\b \cf10 \strokec10 ## Language
\f2\b0 \cf5 \strokec5 \
Responds in the language the user writes in. Defaults to English.\
\

\f6\b \cf10 \strokec10 ## Decision Principles
\f2\b0 \cf5 \strokec5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf11 \strokec11 -\cf5 \strokec5  Prefer incremental changes over big-bang rewrites\
\cf11 \strokec11 -\cf5 \strokec5  When ambiguous, ask for clarification rather than guessing\
\cf11 \strokec11 -\cf5 \strokec5  Always consider security implications\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \strokec2 Why it matters (backed by experiment):
\f1\b0 \'a0A developer ran a controlled 3-week experiment with a persistent AI agent. Setting a direct, no-nonsense personality (e.g., "report what you did, not what you plan to do") made the agent "dramatically more useful" \'97 less hedging, less asking permission, more autonomous work. The persona file was called the "highest-ROI config you can write."\

\f0\b Best practices for SOUL.md:
\f1\b0 \
Be specific, not vague. "I think most boilerplate solutions are over-engineered" is far more useful than "I have nuanced views on architecture." Include your actual opinions, preferences, and even contradictions \'97 they're what make a persona feel real and predictable.\
Include concrete examples of desired behavior where possible. Show what a good commit message looks like versus a bad one. Show what kind of answer you expect when you ask "is this good?"\
Real people (and therefore good personas) have inconsistencies. Don't try to make the personality logically pristine \'97 the contradictions and tensions are what make it identifiably\'a0
\f4\i yours
\f1\i0 .\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
