\f0\b\fs24 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 11. Memory System \'97 MEMORY.md, Daily Logs & Working Memory\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \cf2 This is where the agent becomes stateful \'97 capable of learning, remembering, and maintaining continuity across sessions. The memory system has two layers:\'a0
\f0\b remembrance
\f1\b0 \'a0(what the agent knows) and\'a0
\f0\b personalization
\f1\b0 \'a0(how the agent behaves, covered by SOUL/IDENTITY/USER).\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf2 11a. The Four Types of Agent Memory\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Short-term memory
\f1\b0 \'a0is the agent's immediate context window \'97 the current conversation and recent tool outputs. It's analogous to a human's active attention span and lasts minutes.\

\f0\b Long-term memory (MEMORY.md)
\f1\b0 \'a0is persistent storage of curated facts, preferences, key decisions, and learned lessons that survive across sessions. This file is loaded into every conversation. Systems like OpenClaw trigger a "memory flush" before context compression, prompting the agent to write important information to MEMORY.md before older context is discarded.\

\f0\b Working memory (task_plan.md / todo.md)
\f1\b0 \'a0is a temporary scratchpad for the current task's goals, progress, and intermediate reasoning. Manus popularized a three-file variant:\'a0
\f2 task_plan.md
\f1 \'a0for goals and progress tracking,\'a0
\f2 notes.md
\f1 \'a0for research findings, and an output deliverable file. The agent follows a read-decide-act-update cycle: read the plan, act on the next step, update progress, repeat. This prevents "goal drift" in long-running tasks \'97 Manus found that by constantly rewriting the todo list, the agent pushes its global plan into the model's recent attention span, avoiding the "lost-in-the-middle" problem.\

\f0\b Procedural memory (SKILL.md)
\f1\b0 \'a0is learned workflows and "how-to" knowledge. Rather than loading all possible skills at startup, sophisticated agents load specific skill documentation on-demand, keeping the context manageable.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf2 11b. MEMORY.md \'97 Long-Term Curated Knowledge\
\pard\pardeftab720\qc\partightenfactor0

