\f0\b\fs24 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 16. The Golden Rules\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 Start small, iterate.
\f1\b0 \'a0Begin with 10\'9615 lines covering basics. Add rules as you discover gaps. Your configuration should evolve with your workflow.\

\f0\b Be specific, not vague.
\f1\b0 \'a0"Use early returns to reduce nesting. Max function length: 25 lines" beats "Write good code" every time.\

\f0\b Version control everything.
\f1\b0 \'a0These files are arguably the most important part of your project's documentation. Review changes in PRs.\

\f0\b Treat compaction as sleep, not death.
\f1\b0 \'a0Build your memory files to be the foundation the agent rebuilds from.\

\f0\b Raw logs beat curated summaries.
\f1\b0 \'a0Preserve the messy reality \'97 the debugging sessions, failed attempts, and uncertainty.\

\f0\b Persona isn't fluff \'97 it's the highest-ROI config you can write.
\f1\b0 \'a0A direct, clear personality specification transforms agent output quality.\

\f0\b The master file is the highest leverage point in your entire setup.
\f1\b0 \'a0Every bad line multiplies across every session, every plan, and every line of code. Craft it by hand with care.\
